# Phone app USB deploy

After building or changing the Android app, do **not** use `adb install -r` alone when deploying to a connected phone.

Always use the full restart workflow so the new APK is loaded:

```powershell
cd phone-app
.\gradlew.bat assembleDebug
.\install-debug.ps1
```

Or run the equivalent steps manually:

```powershell
adb shell am force-stop com.example.fuelmonitor
adb install -r phone-app\app\build\outputs\apk\debug\app-debug.apk
adb shell am start -n com.example.fuelmonitor/.MainActivity
```

`adb install -r` only replaces the package on disk. A running app keeps the old in-memory process until force-stopped or manually reopened.
